SFO SKY SCOOP
SFO HELICOPTER AIRLINES, INC., P. O. Box 2525, Oakland, CA 94614
5/71
April 25th has
already passed and we didn't change our schedule.
Since many of the
carriers had major changes due in May and
June, we felt it best
to wait
until these changes
were firm. Our new schedule will become effective on June 1, 1971.
There will be no changes in our Oakland/San Francisco service.
Two additional flights
have been added to our Berkeley and Marin County routes in response to passenger requests.
The following is the new Berkeley/Marin County schedule.
You might note that there have
been some minor changes on flight times to improve our connections to and from other airlines.

In our last issue of the Sky Scoop, we introduced our first and only stewardess,
MARLINE CHERRY.
Passenger reaction
has been so
favorable we have recently added two add i-
tional stewardesses to our flights. We think this feminine touch will be a welcome sight
for our passengers.
Plans are currently in the mill which will enable our travel agent
friends to issue the
scenic excursion tickets mentioned in the last issue of the Sky Scoop.
Last but not least--GIVE US A WHIRL! .....and have a nice day.

properties.sfomuseum:description: Timetable issued by SFO Helicopter Airlines, effective May 1971; titled “SFO Sky Scoop” with schedules for San Francisco, Marin County, and Berkeley flights; on reverse, black and white photographic image of four helicopters in air over San Francisco International Airport; air traffic control tower visible at right.
